---
title: Creamy Dill Chicken with Couscous & Asparagus
description: Creamy mustard dill sauce elevates tender pork filets to an impressive meal that comes together in record time. The savory sauce is spooned over the roasted pork and served with roasted asparagus and buttery couscous to soak up every bit of flavor. With a final sprinkle of fresh dill and chili flakes, this weeknight meal is destined to impress.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67ee99e6469445a3c3f3cea5-0861f17e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67ee99e6469445a3c3f3cea5-en-US.pdf
cuisine: North America
author: Michelle Doll Olson
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/creamy-dill-chicken-67ee99e6469445a3c3f3cea5
time required: 30 minutes
servings: 2
course: main course
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 31 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 35 g
  sugar: 4 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 650 mg
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Line a #baking sheet{} with foil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and discard woody bottom ends from @asparagus{6%ounce}. Pick and roughly chop fronds from @dill{¼%ounce}.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add pork and sear, turning occasionally, until browned all over, ~{4-8%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in the next step).

Turn off heat; transfer pork to one side of prepared baking sheet.

Add asparagus to opposite side of baking sheet from pork; toss with a drizzle of @olive oil{}, @salt{}, @pepper{}, and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} to taste.

Roast on top rack until asparagus is tender and pork is cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Remove from oven; transfer pork to a #cutting board{} to rest for ~{5%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add @Israeli couscous{2.5%ounce} and 1 TBSP @butter{1%tbsp} to a small #pot{} over medium-high heat. Cook, stirring, until butter has melted and couscous is lightly toasted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @water{¾%cup}, half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}, and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}. Drain excess water if necessary. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While couscous cooks, heat pan used for pork over medium-high heat. Add remaining stock concentrates and @water{¼%cup}; bring to a simmer and cook ~{1-2%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low and whisk in @sour cream{3%tablespoon}, half the chopped dill, and @Dijon mustard{2%teaspoon} to taste. Turn off heat. Stir in 1 TBSP @butter{1%tbsp} and any resting juices from pork. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fluff couscous with a fork and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide couscous, pork, and asparagus between plates. Spoon sauce over pork and sprinkle with remaining chopped dill and @chili flakes{} to taste. Serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.